    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">You are given one variable that is modified by a sequence of operations.<br>The variable starts at <const>0</const>.<br>Each operation changes the value by either addition (<const>+</const>) or subtraction (<const>-</const>).<br>Your task is to compute the final value after applying all operations in order.</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1</strong>: An integer <var>n</var> &mdash; the number of operations.<br><strong>Next <var>n</var> lines</strong>: Each line contains one operation in the form <const>+</const><var>x</var> or <const>-</const><var>x</var>, describing how the variable changes.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\"><strong>Line 1</strong>:<br>The final value of the variable after all operations have been applied.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">2 &le; <var>n</var> &le; 10<br>&minus;10⁶ &le; <var>x</var> &le; 10⁶</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">3\n+5\n-2\n+7</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-out\">10</pre>\n         </div>\n      </div>\n   </div>\n</div>"
